The article is a speech given by the First Lady of Houston, Texas, addressing parents and encouraging them to get their children vaccinated against COVID-19. She acknowledges the challenges parents have faced during the pandemic, including supporting virtual learning and finding ways to keep their children socially engaged. The First Lady emphasizes the importance of protecting children's health and assures parents that the vaccine is safe, free, and available for all children aged five and up. She mentions the existence of pop-up vaccination clinics in the city and encourages parents to make the decision to vaccinate their children, as it is a crucial step in keeping them safe.